About this property
Charming Lakefront Bala Cottage
This charming, cozy, 4 season cottage overlooks the Moon River in the heart of Bala, just 12 minutes off the 400! With over a half-acre of land, this gem is located within minutes to the grocery store, Don’s Bakery, Beer Store, LCBO, The Kee, markets, the beach, hiking trails, snowmobile trails & more.

2 minutes to Bala (15 min walk)
10 minutes to Port Carling
15 minutes to Gravenhurst
25 minutes to Bracebridge

Cottage is fully equipped for you to enjoy, just bring your personal items!

This recently renovated cottage is full of things to do!

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)
High Season - June - Aug (7 night minimum stay, check-in on Friday)

Dock - The floating dock will be available for use from May long weekend until Thanksgiving.

Winter Access - The cottage is located off a main road that is plowed by the city. The cottage driveway will be cleared by a snow removal company we have hired each time there is a large snowfall.

About the area
Bala
Located in Muskoka Lakes, this cottage is on the waterfront. The area's natural beauty can be seen at Lake Muskoka and Hardy Lake Provincial Park, while Bala's Museum and Muskoka Lakes Museum are cultural highlights. Discover the area's water adventures with jet skiing, kayaking and waterskiing nearby, or enjoy the great outdoors with hiking/biking trails.

About the host
Hosted by Jessica Page
Our family currently lives in Oakville but love to escape to our cottage in Muskoka for a restful break and to enjoy our coffee on the dock, swimming in the lake and walks through nature. We will be available at all times before and during your stay to answer any questions you may have. We are happy to provide recommendations for things to do in the area!

About this property
Charming Lakefront Bala Cottage
This charming, cozy, 4 season cottage overlooks the Moon River in the heart of Bala, just 12 minutes off the 400! With over a half-acre of land, this gem is located within minutes to the grocery store, Don’s Bakery, Beer Store, LCBO, The Kee, markets, the beach, hiking trails, snowmobile trails & more.

2 minutes to Bala (15 min walk)
10 minutes to Port Carling
15 minutes to Gravenhurst
25 minutes to Bracebridge

Cottage is fully equipped for you to enjoy, just bring your personal items!

This recently renovated cottage is full of things to do!

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)
High Season - June - Aug (7 night minimum stay, check-in on Friday)

Dock - The floating dock will be available for use from May long weekend until Thanksgiving.

Winter Access - The cottage is located off a main road that is plowed by the city. The cottage driveway will be cleared by a snow removal company we have hired each time there is a large snowfall.

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)
High Season - June - Aug (7 night minimum stay, check-in on Friday)

Dock - The floating dock will be available for use from May long weekend until Thanksgiving.

Winter Access - The cottage is located off a main road that is plowed by the city. The cottage driveway will be cleared by a snow removal company we have hired each time there is a large snowfall.

About this property
Charming Lakefront Bala Cottage
This charming, cozy, 4 season cottage overlooks the Moon River in the heart of Bala, just 12 minutes off the 400! With over a half-acre of land, this gem is located within minutes to the grocery store, Don’s Bakery, Beer Store, LCBO, The Kee, markets, the beach, hiking trails, snowmobile trails & more.

2 minutes to Bala (15 min walk)
10 minutes to Port Carling
15 minutes to Gravenhurst
25 minutes to Bracebridge

Cottage is fully equipped for you to enjoy, just bring your personal items!

This recently renovated cottage is full of things to do!

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)

About the area
Bala
Located in Muskoka Lakes, this cottage is on the waterfront. The area's natural beauty can be seen at Lake Muskoka and Hardy Lake Provincial Park, while Bala's Museum and Muskoka Lakes Museum are cultural highlights. Discover the area's water adventures with jet skiing, kayaking and waterskiing nearby, or enjoy the great outdoors with hiking/biking trails.

About this property
Charming Lakefront Bala Cottage
This charming, cozy, 4 season cottage overlooks the Moon River in the heart of Bala, just 12 minutes off the 400! With over a half-acre of land, this gem is located within minutes to the grocery store, Don’s Bakery, Beer Store, LCBO, The Kee, markets, the beach, hiking trails, snowmobile trails & more.

2 minutes to Bala (15 min walk)
10 minutes to Port Carling
15 minutes to Gravenhurst
25 minutes to Bracebridge

Cottage is fully equipped for you to enjoy, just bring your personal items!

This recently renovated cottage is full of things to do!

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)
High Season - June - Aug (7 night minimum stay, check-in on Friday)

Dock - The floating dock will be available for use from May long weekend until Thanksgiving.

Winter Access - The cottage is located off a main road that is plowed by the city. The cottage driveway will be cleared by a snow removal company we have hired each time there is a large snowfall.

Jessica Page

About the area
Bala
Located in Muskoka Lakes, this cottage is on the waterfront. The area's natural beauty can be seen at Lake Muskoka and Hardy Lake Provincial Park, while Bala's Museum and Muskoka Lakes Museum are cultural highlights. Discover the area's water adventures with jet skiing, kayaking and waterskiing nearby, or enjoy the great outdoors with hiking/biking trails.

About this property
Charming Lakefront Bala Cottage
This charming, cozy, 4 season cottage overlooks the Moon River in the heart of Bala, just 12 minutes off the 400! With over a half-acre of land, this gem is located within minutes to the grocery store, Don’s Bakery, Beer Store, LCBO, The Kee, markets, the beach, hiking trails, snowmobile trails & more.

2 minutes to Bala (15 min walk)
10 minutes to Port Carling
15 minutes to Gravenhurst
25 minutes to Bracebridge

Cottage is fully equipped for you to enjoy, just bring your personal items!

This recently renovated cottage is full of things to do!

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)
High Season - June - Aug (7 night minimum stay, check-in on Friday)

Dock - The floating dock will be available for use from May long weekend until Thanksgiving.

Winter Access - The cottage is located off a main road that is plowed by the city. The cottage driveway will be cleared by a snow removal company we have hired each time there is a large snowfall.

About the area
Bala
Located in Muskoka Lakes, this cottage is on the waterfront. The area's natural beauty can be seen at Lake Muskoka and Hardy Lake Provincial Park, while Bala's Museum and Muskoka Lakes Museum are cultural highlights. Discover the area's water adventures with jet skiing, kayaking and waterskiing nearby, or enjoy the great outdoors with hiking/biking trails.

About this property
Charming Lakefront Bala Cottage
This charming, cozy, 4 season cottage overlooks the Moon River in the heart of Bala, just 12 minutes off the 400! With over a half-acre of land, this gem is located within minutes to the grocery store, Don’s Bakery, Beer Store, LCBO, The Kee, markets, the beach, hiking trails, snowmobile trails & more.

2 minutes to Bala (15 min walk)
10 minutes to Port Carling
15 minutes to Gravenhurst
25 minutes to Bracebridge

Cottage is fully equipped for you to enjoy, just bring your personal items!

This recently renovated cottage is full of things to do!

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)
High Season - June - Aug (7 night minimum stay, check-in on Friday)

Dock - The floating dock will be available for use from May long weekend until Thanksgiving.

Winter Access - The cottage is located off a main road that is plowed by the city. The cottage driveway will be cleared by a snow removal company we have hired each time there is a large snowfall.

About the area
Bala
Located in Muskoka Lakes, this cottage is on the waterfront. The area's natural beauty can be seen at Lake Muskoka and Hardy Lake Provincial Park, while Bala's Museum and Muskoka Lakes Museum are cultural highlights. Discover the area's water adventures with jet skiing, kayaking and waterskiing nearby, or enjoy the great outdoors with hiking/biking trails.

About this property
Charming Lakefront Bala Cottage
This charming, cozy, 4 season cottage overlooks the Moon River in the heart of Bala, just 12 minutes off the 400! With over a half-acre of land, this gem is located within minutes to the grocery store, Don’s Bakery, Beer Store, LCBO, The Kee, markets, the beach, hiking trails, snowmobile trails & more.

2 minutes to Bala (15 min walk)
10 minutes to Port Carling
15 minutes to Gravenhurst
25 minutes to Bracebridge

Cottage is fully equipped for you to enjoy, just bring your personal items!

This recently renovated cottage is full of things to do!

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)
High Season - June - Aug (7 night minimum stay, check-in on Friday)

Dock - The floating dock will be available for use from May long weekend until Thanksgiving.

Winter Access - The cottage is located off a main road that is plowed by the city. The cottage driveway will be cleared by a snow removal company we have hired each time there is a large snowfall.

I would love to see this place in the fall.

About this property
Charming Lakefront Bala Cottage
This charming, cozy, 4 season cottage overlooks the Moon River in the heart of Bala, just 12 minutes off the 400! With over a half-acre of land, this gem is located within minutes to the grocery store, Don’s Bakery, Beer Store, LCBO, The Kee, markets, the beach, hiking trails, snowmobile trails & more.

2 minutes to Bala (15 min walk)
10 minutes to Port Carling
15 minutes to Gravenhurst
25 minutes to Bracebridge

Cottage is fully equipped for you to enjoy, just bring your personal items!

This recently renovated cottage is full of things to do!

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)
High Season - June - Aug (7 night minimum stay, check-in on Friday)

Dock - The floating dock will be available for use from May long weekend until Thanksgiving.

Winter Access - The cottage is located off a main road that is plowed by the city. The cottage driveway will be cleared by a snow removal company we have hired each time there is a large snowfall.
Property manager
Jessica Page

structured_data.text:
About this property
Charming Lakefront Bala Cottage
This charming, cozy, 4 season cottage overlooks the Moon River in the heart of Bala, just 12 minutes off the 400! With over a half-acre of land, this gem is located within minutes to the grocery store, Don’s Bakery, Beer Store, LCBO, The Kee, markets, the beach, hiking trails, snowmobile trails & more.

2 minutes to Bala (15 min walk)
10 minutes to Port Carling
15 minutes to Gravenhurst
25 minutes to Bracebridge

Cottage is fully equipped for you to enjoy, just bring your personal items!

This recently renovated cottage is full of things to do!

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)
High Season - June - Aug (7 night minimum stay, check-in on Friday)

Dock - The floating dock will be available for use from May long weekend until Thanksgiving.

Winter Access - The cottage is located off a main road that is plowed by the city. The cottage driveway will be cleared by a snow removal company we have hired each time there is a large snowfall.
Property manager
Jessica Page
Languages
English

With over a half-acre of land, this gem is located within minutes to the grocery store, Don’s Bakery, Beer Store, LCBO, The Kee, markets, the beach, hiking trails, snowmobile trails & more.

2 minutes to Bala (15 min walk)
10 minutes to Port Carling
15 minutes to Gravenhurst
25 minutes to Bracebridge

Cottage is fully equipped for you to enjoy, just bring your personal items!

This recently renovated cottage is full of things to do!

In the warmer months, enjoy the use of our two kayaks around the lake, enjoy a great book on the dock, gather on the lakeside deck equipped with a built-in bench & high top table, and enjoy quality time around the outdoor fire pit.

In the cooler months, enjoy the fall foliage or snow covered trees from the cottage, enjoy the hiking, ice skating and snowmobile trails in the area, challenge your friends or family to a board game, curl up beside the fireplace and watch your favourite shows and movies.

The cottage is fully winterized with baseboard heaters as well as an indoor fireplace. In the summer months, air conditioning is available.

All bedrooms are equipped with new beds, pillows, sheets, quilt set and comforters.

The kitchen is fully equipped for you to cook your favourite meals and enjoy around the dining table with your family and friends. There is a propane BBQ to grill your favourites!

The laundry area has a new washing machine and dryer if you choose to use them.

There are floaties for you to enjoy during your stay.

Cottage is equipped with a smart TV, wifi & cable.

Low Season - September-May (2 night minimum)
High Season - June - Aug (7 night minimum stay, check-in on Friday)

Dock - The floating dock will be available for use from May long weekend until Thanksgiving.

Winter Access - The cottage is located off a main road that is plowed by the city. The cottage driveway will be cleared by a snow removal company we have hired each time there is a large snowfall.
Property manager
Jessica Page
Languages
English
